The paper proposes a new algorithm for solving non-convex optimization problems with sparsity-inducing penalties, which is a common problem in machine learning and data science. The paper discusses the convergence analysis of the proposed algorithm and demonstrates its efficiency through experiments on large-scale datasets. Based on this, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
